scream /skriːm/

(screaming,screamed,screams) 

1. V-I When someone screams , they make a very loud, high-pitched cry, for example, because they are in pain or are very frightened. (人因痛苦或恐惧而) 尖叫 

例： Women were screaming; some of the houses nearest the bridge were on fire. 女人们在尖叫；最靠近桥的一些房屋在燃烧。 

2. N-COUNT Scream is also a noun. 尖叫 

例： Hilda let out a scream. 希尔达发出了一声尖叫。 

3. V-T If you scream something, you shout it in a loud, high-pitched voice. 尖声说 

例： 'Brigid!' she screamed. 'Get up!' “布里吉德！”她尖声叫道。“起床！”

